This paper deals with instance-level segmentation in the context of autonomous driving, which is a problem that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of a Markov random field (MRF) model, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper is focused on improving the performance of autonomous driving systems, which is a topic relevant to computer networks and communications (cs.CR).
